{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2edbc911-f78f-4b4e-b6db-0d133376a582","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility bridge by default.**\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK shipped with `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge` set to `true`, so `vstest.console.exe` could still discover and run tests. In 4.x, that default flipped to `false` — meaning `vstest.console` sees zero tests.\n\n### You have two options\n\n**Option A** – Re-enable the bridge (quick CI fix):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Option B (recommended)** – Stop using `vstest.console` and switch your CI to:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test          # uses the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively\n```\n\nor run the test executable directly:\n\n```bash\n./TestProject --results-directory ./results\n```\n\nOption B is the intended migration path — the new platform is faster and doesn't need the VSTest adapter layer.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6092ad8d-1018-49a1-a8af-0b9069cbd62e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest SDK. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8 / MSTest 3.8, and more definitively in MSTest 4.x, the VSTest compatibility layer was removed by default. MSTest.Sdk 4.x uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the new test platform) as the default runner and no longer ships the VSTest adapter/bridge by default.\n\nKey change: In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge` property defaults to `false`, meaning `vstest.console.exe` can no longer discover or run tests. \n\nWith 4.x, tests now run as a self-contained executable, so `dotnet test` continues to work since it was updated to support the new platform, but `vstest.console.exe` specifically won't work. The solution is either switching your CI to use `dotnet test` or the test executable directly, or re-enabling the VSTest bridge by setting `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge` to `true` in your project file.","outputTokens":573,"requestId":"7C14:1EDE:8D2CC2:A63DA3:69F960CB"},"id":"d6df2c97-573c-4ea8-a1f5-d8b19692ba6c","timestamp":"2026-05-05T03:15:36.480Z","parentId":"4ff93205-8de3-46d5-8a99-f66bd3bd0946"}
